modules.description: Provides serialization and deserialization between a type `t` and S-expressions using `sexp_of_t` and `t_of_sexp`. Works with arbitrary data types that have S-expression representations. Used to convert internal data structures to and from a textual format for logging or configuration parsing.

Provides bitwise operations on binary vectors, including packing and unpacking values into S-expressions. Works with arbitrary-length bit vectors and integer types, supporting serialization and deserialization. Used to encode and decode protocol buffers or custom binary formats in network communication.

Serializes and deserializes values of type `t` to and from S-expressions, enabling easy integration with text-based configurations and logs. Supports arbitrary data types with S-expression encodings, allowing structured data to be represented and parsed as symbolic expressions. For example, a custom record can be converted to a list of symbols and values, or parsed back into its original form. Operations include converting a value to an S-expression, parsing an S-expression into a value, and handling nested structures seamlessly.
